Whereas the rate of growth in Federal spending over the
			 past decade is 64 percent and the rate of growth in Federal revenues for the
			 same period is 37 percent, a difference of 27 percentage points;

Whereas the national debt exceeds $16 trillion dollars
			 and, according to the non-partisan Congressional Budget Office, is expected to
			 reach $20 trillion by 2022;

Whereas absent any change in policy, entitlement spending
			 will consume all Federal revenues by 2049, according to the Congressional
			 Budget Office;
